tafsir[6]{c,v,t}:
  55,46,"(But for him who feareth the standing before his Lord) but he who fears standing before his Lord upon being on the verge of committing a transgression and thus desists from it (there are two Gardens) the Garden of Eden and the Firdaws."
  55,48,"Of spreading branches) and different kinds."
  55,52,"(Wherein is every kind of fruit in pairs) both with regard to shape and taste."
  55,58,"(In beauty) like the jacynth and the coral stone."
  55,60,"Is the reward of goodness aught save goodness?) He says: is the reward of he whom We have blessed with the profession of Allah's divine Oneness anything but the Garden?"
  55,64,"(Dark green with foliage) because of their abundant watering."